name: Energy-Management-System
description: I developed an Energy Management System that consists of four microservices (User, Device, Monitoring and Communication, Chat), built using Java Spring, a frontend component developed in ReactJS, and a simulator for the devices. The application utilizes technologies such as RabbitMQ and WebSockets, and all components are deployed using Docker.

name: CurrencyArbitrageAnalyticsEngine
description: Comprehensive system designed to identify and analyze arbitrage opportunities across various currency markets in real-time. It leverages a microservices architecture to efficiently process live data, detect potential arbitrage opportunities, and calculate the associated profit margins after accounting for transaction costs.

name: video-share-back-end
description: The video-share-back-end project is a sophisticated backend system for a video sharing platform, implemented using several microservices. This project leverages Node.js, MQTT, and TypeScript to provide a scalable and efficient architecture for managing video uploads, processing, and sharing.
